message.content:
cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning distributed representations of clinical notes using natural language processing techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an embedding framework that integrates text modeling and semantic correspondence learning into a single model for effective risk assessment.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with predicting patient mortality using electronic health notes and learning patient representations.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with healthcare domain and the ethical implications of using patient data for predictive modeling.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with extracting structured information from unstructured clinical notes for effective risk assessment.
